content: Anyang Art Park is located 2 kilometers northeast of Anyang Station.. This Park comprises dozens of quirky sculptures and installations by Korean and international artists scattered through a verdant valley and along the rocky river bank. Then climb up to Anyang Peak, the 141m-high spiral observatory, for fantastic views across the valley.

There is a lot to eat and there is a valley, so it is cool and a place where you can feel like traveling fun with your friends! It's more like a valley amusement park than a park!! It's like Samseongsan Gwanaksan, so the hiking trail is also good :)
A cultural space used by citizens of Anyang Art Park. Nice forest and various amenities. There is also a valley next to it, and you can use the sour facilities for free in summer.
Going during the cheery blossoms in early April, the atmosphere is very good. cool weather
